rcpDta.text: Angels avert 4-game sweep with 5-4 victory over Red Sox
rcpDta.description: — Hunter Renfroe hit a three-run, first-inning homer and Los Angeles held off the Boston Red Sox 5-4 on Monday in the annual Patriots’ Day game that had Angels’ two-way star Shohei Ohtani’s pitching start shortened by a long rain delay.
